genresAdvancedInfo.name: handbells
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Handbells are a musical instrument that consists of a set of tuned bells that are struck with mallets or hammers. They are often used in church music and other religious settings, but can also be found in secular music as well. Handbells can produce a wide range of sounds, from soft and delicate to loud and powerful, and are often used to create intricate and complex melodies.
